ZZAVNAD is a nanoVNA data viewer which I developed for my own use.

I am now making this publicly available.

Windows Installation
--------------------

A file ZZAVNAD-<[version].msi is available from https://sourceforge/projects/zzavnad. 
Please follow instructions to install this. ZZAVNAD will be installed in 
"C:\Program Files\GM3ZZA\ZZAVNAD\". 
Data used by ZZAVNAD will be installed in "C:\ProgramData\GM3ZZA\ZZAVNAD". 

The source may be cloned from https://github.com/pvrose/zzavnad. 
However this has dependencies on the following libraries: 
FLTK, BOOST and FFTW3. These are not included in the source distribution. 
The documentation also requires the use of Doxygen and LateX.

It may be built using CMake under MSVC. See the appropriate section in the User Guide.



Linux Installation
------------------

ZZAVNAD is available in source form. It may be cloned from 
"https://github.com/pvrose/zzavnad". 
It has dependencies on the external libraries: fltk, hamlib, libcurl and 
nlohmann/json. To date this has only been developed on Debian bookworm.

FLTK can either be compiled from source cloned from github (https://github.com/fltk/fltk) or 
installed form a tarball. It is also available in most distros. Version 1.4.3 
or greater is required.

Doxygen is available in most distros.

The build and install processes use CMake.

For more details see the installation section in the User Guide.